data.shownotes: This show featured the debut of Beginner's Luck. Stu sat in on flute with opener Mild High Club on Sketches of Brunswick East II. Alex Brettin from Mild High Club played guitar for D-Day and The Book. Malcolm Brown (formerly of Whitney) played keyboard on Beginner's Luck.

This show featured the debut of Rock N’ Roll. On The Road Again (Rockets) played as the band came on stage. The vocal intro to Nuclear Fusion was not performed. Han-Tyumi, The Confused Cyborg contained alternate lyrics and Stu on flute. Before Rock N’ Roll, Joey had to gently kick a fan off the stage. Stu later mentioned that they were recording the show that night, and that the unreleased song (Rock N’ Roll) was "kinda new". A pro-shot video of The Fourth Colour was released on the Flightless Records YouTube channel. The Fourth Colour contained a tuning session outro with a droning noise playing in the background, and eventually Cellophane teases. Robot Stop contained Master of the Universe (Hawkwind) teases and quotes, and a Hot Water tease. Malcolm Brown (formerly of Whitney) played keyboard on Beginner's Luck. Stu sat in on flute with opener Mild High Club on Sketches of Brunswick East II.

Surprise show announced the day before. This show featured the debut of Self-Immolate, Mars For The Rich, Venusian 1, Venusian 2, Perihelion, Inner Cell, Loyalty, Horology, Plastic Boogie, This Thing, The Bird Song, Melting, Boogieman Sam, The Cruel Millenial, Acarine, Murder Of The Universe, Planet B, Organ Farmer, Hell and Cyboogie. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete, but only partial recordings are available. Mars For The Rich, Planet B and Cyboogie have been confirmed via audio/video recordings. The remaining songs were confirmed through contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (guest appearances, segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net.

Poster By Jason Galea
Edition of 100

Evil Star was played through the PA speakers before and as the band went on stage. Only Part I of The River was performed and it contained Wah Wah teases. Wah Wah contained The River quotes. This Thing was introduced as a song about Joeys mom. Boogieman Sam was dedicated to their sound tech "Sammy José". Cyboogie was introduced as a song about Stu's grandma by Joey, with him also asking the audience for respect to let Stu sing about his grandma. After Cyboogie, Joey thanked openers ORB and Stonefield.

Poster By Jason Galea
Edition of 200

This show took place at the former Fillmore West space. Evil Star was played through the PA speakers before and as the band came on stage. Joey shouted out The Grateful Dead before Mars For the Rich. I'm Not In Your Mind and I'm In Your Mind Fuzz contained Altered Beast teases. Cellophane contained Alter Me quotes and teases. This Thing was introduced by Joey as a "song about communism." Billabong Valley was introduced by Ambrose as a “song about a bush ranger buddy.” Joey thanked ORB and Stonefield before Perihelion.

Evil Star was played through the PA speakers before and as the band went on stage. Robot Stop contained an Alter Me tease. The Bitter Boogie contained Cut Throat Boogie quotes and Cyboogie teases.

Poster By Jason Galea
Edition of 160

Evil Star was played through the PA speakers as the band came on stage. Joey dedicated Cyboogie to "the internet". Boogieman Sam was dedicated to "Sammy Boy". The Bitter Boogie contained Cyboogie teases, Cut Throat Boogie quotes and teases, and Boogieman Sam quotes. This show was released through the Official Bootlegger program as Live in Asheville ‘19. Evil Star was played through the PA speakers before the show. I'm Not In Your Mind contained Robot Stop teases. Beginner's Luck featured Stu on flute. Following Beginner's Luck, the band played a short parody country song. Rattlesnake contained a Honey intro tease. Beginner’s Luck was released as a bonus feature for the 'Chunky Shrapnel' concert film.
